# Data Consistency Integration Tests
# Verifies data integrity across all operations and modules

### Variables
@baseUrl = https://localhost:7001/api
@adminToken = your-admin-token-here
@teacherToken = your-teacher-token-here
@studentToken = your-student-token-here

### TEST 1: Question-Exam Relationship Consistency

### Create question
POST {{baseUrl}}/cauhoi
Authorization: Bearer {{teacherToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "noiDung": "Data consistency test question",
  "idDanhMuc": 1,
  "idLoai": 1,
  "mucDo": 2,
  "dapAnA": "Option A",
  "dapAnB": "Option B",
  "dapAnC": "Option C",
  "dapAnD": "Option D",
  "dapAnDung": "A",
  "giaiThich": "Test explanation"
}

@questionId = {{$response.body.$.data.id}}

### Create exam with the question
POST {{baseUrl}}/exam
Authorization: Bearer {{teacherToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "tenDeThi": "Data Consistency Test Exam",
  "moTa": "Testing data relationships",
  "thoiGianLamBai": 30,
  "soLuongCauHoi": 1,
  "trangThai": true,
  "ngayBatDau": "2026-05-20T09:00:00",
  "ngayKetThuc": "2026-05-20T18:00:00",
  "cauHoiIds": [{{questionId}}]
}

@examId = {{$response.body.$.data.id}}

### Verify question appears in exam
GET {{baseUrl}}/exam/{{examId}}/questions
Authorization: Bearer {{teacherToken}}

### Verify exam references question correctly
GET {{baseUrl}}/cauhoi/{{questionId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{teacherToken}}

### TEST 2: Session-Answer Relationship Consistency

### Start exam session
POST {{baseUrl}}/exam/{{examId}}/start
Authorization: Bearer {{studentToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{}

@sessionId = {{$response.body.$.data.sessionId}}

### Submit answer
POST {{baseUrl}}/exam/{{sessionId}}/answer
Authorization: Bearer {{studentToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "cauHoiId": {{questionId}},
  "dapAnChon": "A",
  "thoiGianTraLoi": 25
}

### Verify answer is linked to correct session
GET {{baseUrl}}/exam/{{sessionId}}/answers
Authorization: Bearer {{teacherToken}}

### Verify session contains correct answer
GET {{baseUrl}}/exam/{{sessionId}}/details
Authorization: Bearer {{teacherToken}}

### TEST 3: Anti-Cheat Log Consistency

### Log anti-cheat event
POST {{baseUrl}}/exam/{{sessionId}}/anticheat
Authorization: Bearer {{studentToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "loaiHanhVi": "SUSPICIOUS_ACTIVITY",
  "thoiGian": "2026-05-20T10:30:00",
  "chiTiet": "Testing data consistency"
}

### Verify anti-cheat log is linked to session
GET {{baseUrl}}/exam/{{sessionId}}/anticheat-logs
Authorization: Bearer {{teacherToken}}

### Submit exam
POST {{baseUrl}}/exam/{{sessionId}}/submit
Authorization: Bearer {{studentToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{}

### TEST 4: Cascade Operations Consistency

### Verify all related data exists before deletion
GET {{baseUrl}}/exam/{{examId}}/sessions
Authorization: Bearer {{teacherToken}}

GET {{baseUrl}}/exam/{{sessionId}}/result
Authorization: Bearer {{teacherToken}}

### TEST 5: Transaction Consistency (Simulated Failure Scenarios)

### Try to create exam with non-existent question (should fail)
POST {{baseUrl}}/exam
Authorization: Bearer {{teacherToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "tenDeThi": "Invalid Exam",
  "moTa": "Should fail due to invalid question ID",
  "thoiGianLamBai": 30,
  "soLuongCauHoi": 1,
  "trangThai": true,
  "ngayBatDau": "2026-05-20T09:00:00",
  "ngayKetThuc": "2026-05-20T18:00:00",
  "cauHoiIds": [99999]
}

### Try to answer non-existent question (should fail)
POST {{baseUrl}}/exam/{{sessionId}}/answer
Authorization: Bearer {{studentToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "cauHoiId": 99999,
  "dapAnChon": "A",
  "thoiGianTraLoi": 25
}

### Try to start exam that doesn't exist (should fail)
POST {{baseUrl}}/exam/99999/start
Authorization: Bearer {{studentToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{}

### TEST 6: Data Integrity After Updates

### Update question content
PUT {{baseUrl}}/cauhoi/{{questionId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{teacherToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "noiDung": "Updated question content for consistency test",
  "idDanhMuc": 1,
  "idLoai": 1,
  "mucDo": 2,
  "dapAnA": "Updated Option A",
  "dapAnB": "Updated Option B",
  "dapAnC": "Updated Option C",
  "dapAnD": "Updated Option D",
  "dapAnDung": "A",
  "giaiThich": "Updated explanation"
}

### Verify exam still references updated question correctly
GET {{baseUrl}}/exam/{{examId}}/questions
Authorization: Bearer {{teacherToken}}

### Verify existing answers remain consistent
GET {{baseUrl}}/exam/{{sessionId}}/answers
Authorization: Bearer {{teacherToken}}

### TEST 7: Concurrent Data Modification Consistency

### Create second session for same exam
POST {{baseUrl}}/exam/{{examId}}/start
Authorization: Bearer {{studentToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{}

@session2Id = {{$response.body.$.data.sessionId}}

### Both sessions should see same question data
GET {{baseUrl}}/exam/{{sessionId}}/questions
Authorization: Bearer {{studentToken}}

GET {{baseUrl}}/exam/{{session2Id}}/questions
Authorization: Bearer {{studentToken}}

### Submit different answers from both sessions
POST {{baseUrl}}/exam/{{session2Id}}/answer
Authorization: Bearer {{studentToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "cauHoiId": {{questionId}},
  "dapAnChon": "B",
  "thoiGianTraLoi": 30
}

### Submit second session
POST {{baseUrl}}/exam/{{session2Id}}/submit
Authorization: Bearer {{studentToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{}

### Verify both sessions have independent results
GET {{baseUrl}}/exam/{{sessionId}}/result
Authorization: Bearer {{teacherToken}}

GET {{baseUrl}}/exam/{{session2Id}}/result
Authorization: Bearer {{teacherToken}}

### TEST 8: Foreign Key Constraint Verification

### Try to delete question that's used in exam (should fail or handle gracefully)
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/cauhoi/{{questionId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

### Verify question still exists
GET {{baseUrl}}/cauhoi/{{questionId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{teacherToken}}

### Verify exam still works
GET {{baseUrl}}/exam/{{examId}}/questions
Authorization: Bearer {{teacherToken}}

### TEST 9: Data Consistency After System Operations

### Get comprehensive exam statistics
GET {{baseUrl}}/exam/{{examId}}/statistics
Authorization: Bearer {{teacherToken}}

### Verify statistics match actual data
GET {{baseUrl}}/exam/{{examId}}/results
Authorization: Bearer {{teacherToken}}

### Cross-check session count
GET {{baseUrl}}/exam/{{examId}}/sessions
Authorization: Bearer {{teacherToken}}

### TEST 10: Audit Trail Consistency

### Check if all operations are properly logged
GET {{baseUrl}}/admin/audit-logs?examId={{examId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

### Verify timestamps are consistent
GET {{baseUrl}}/exam/{{sessionId}}/timeline
Authorization: Bearer {{teacherToken}}

### CLEANUP AND FINAL VERIFICATION

### Delete exam (should cascade properly)
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/exam/{{examId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

### Verify sessions are deleted
GET {{baseUrl}}/exam/{{sessionId}}/details
Authorization: Bearer {{teacherToken}}

### Verify answers are deleted
GET {{baseUrl}}/exam/{{sessionId}}/answers
Authorization: Bearer {{teacherToken}}

### Verify anti-cheat logs are deleted
GET {{baseUrl}}/exam/{{sessionId}}/anticheat-logs
Authorization: Bearer {{teacherToken}}

### Question should still exist (not cascaded)
GET {{baseUrl}}/cauhoi/{{questionId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{teacherToken}}

### Clean up question
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/cauhoi/{{questionId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

### EXPECTED RESULTS:
# - All foreign key relationships should be maintained
# - No orphaned records should exist
# - Updates should not break existing relationships
# - Cascade deletes should work properly
# - Concurrent operations should not corrupt data
# - Failed operations should not leave partial data
# - All timestamps should be consistent and logical
# - Statistics should match actual data counts
# - Audit trails should be complete and accurate